{"parentUuid": "dcc2f824-5756-4821-bf76-73335f7bb4bf", "isSidechain": false, "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_13e378ba-96e", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The flake is almost certainly the navigation race: `toHaveURL` polls but starts immediately, and on cold CI runners the redirect can take 3-4s after the click. Switched to `waitForURL` with an explicit timeout \u2014 Playwright will wait for the actual navigation event rather than polling the URL string. Also worth checking that your test runs aren't sharing storage state between workers; each worker should get a fresh context."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"input_tokens": 433, "output_tokens": 171, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 9778}}, "requestId": "req_60ac3d38-fa9", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "ed0156e9-d8f3-4844-8609-b31073084120", "timestamp": "2026-05-07T07:00:50.000Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/nextjs-app", "sessionId": "c1b017f2-9032-4d5b-b426-98e253423a1d", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
